> Dear Martin,
>
> The answer is no. The standard error is not a measure of dispersion of 
> the data, but a measure of the imprecision of estimation. A large 
> standard error may come from large variability between data, but also 
> from small sample size. The standard error becomes always small if the 
> sample size becomes large (law of large numbers).
>
> Best,
>
> Gerta
